data.BKG: Bulk Bag - A large sized flexible, intermediate bulk container; the side walls are flexible; it's made of fabric; when filled, it takes on the shape of what you put inside
data.BOT: Bottle - A container having a round neck of relatively smaller diameter than the body with an opening that can be fitted with lid; it does not have a handle
data.CNB: Container, MAC-ISO (Military Airlift Container - International Standards Organization) Light Weight 8x8x20 Foot Air - An air container conforming to ISO standards
data.CNF: Multiwall Container Secured to Warehouse Pallet
data.CNX: CONEX - Container Express - An 8x8x8-foot container used for packaging and shipping military material
data.CUB: Cube - A box that has a "bladder" (poly-formed bladder) inside; it has an opening similar to bottle; the interior bladder is flexible not rigid
data.DRM: Drum - A large container with a cylindrical shape; top may have removable or sealed top sides may be fiberboard or metal
data.FLX: Liner Bag Liquid - A rubber liner used in a standard container for liquid material
data.HRB: On Hanger or Rack in Boxes
data.JUG: Jug - A bottle (usually 1/2 gallon or larger) fitted with a handle
data.MLV: MILVAN - Military Van - A 20-foot transportation van that conforms to ISO standards
data.MSV: MSCVAN - Military Sealift Command Van - A 35-foot transportation van
data.OVW: Overwrap - A cardboard bottom is put down on a pallet; the bags are stacked in layers; the top of the cardboard slides down over the bags to meet the bottom; if any of the bags tear, the product always stays inside the cardboard
data.SBC: Liner Bag Dry - A plastic liner used in container designed for the carriage of dry free-flowing material
data.SLP: Slip Sheet - Shipping containers utilizing slip sheets, which are cardboard platforms used to hold product for storage or transportation
data.SVN: SEAVAN - Sea Van - A commercial or military 40-foot transportation container that conforms to ISO standards
data.TRI: Triwall Box - A sturdy box made of three-ply cardboard
data.TTC: Tote Can - A reusable stainless steel container with handles; used for liquid material
